posts.title: 2024 Presidential Debate: President Donald J. Trump vs. Vice President Kamala Harris - LIVE at 9 PM
posts.content:
Hello, fellow patriots! Gather your loved ones and pets. It's time for a Presidential Debate with your favorite President and mine: Donald J. Trump!

President Donald Trump and Vice President Kamala Harris face off tonight in their first, and possibly only, Presidential debate of the 2024 election season. The debate takes place in Philadelphia at the National Constitution Center. ABC News will host the debate, which starts at 9 PM Trump/Eastern Time and will run 90 minutes with two commercial breaks. The moderators for tonight's debate will be David Muir, anchor of ABC World News Tonight, and Linsey Davis, anchor of ABC News Live Prime.

Other important dates:

  • October 1st - Vice-Presidential debate is hosted by CBS News in New York City.
  • Nomember 5th - Election Day in the United States. Vote for Trump!
  • December 17 - Electors cast their votes for President Trump and Vice President Vance.
  • January 20 - President Trump and Vice President Vance are sworn into office.

Rules:

  • There will be no live audience.
  • There will be no opening statements.
  • Candidates will be introduced by the moderators, starting with Vice President Harris.
  • Candidates will have two minutes to answer questions, two minutes for rebuttals, and an additional minute for follow-ups.
  • Candidates will have up to two minutes each for closing statements at the end.
  • Candidates are not permitted to ask questions of each other.
  • Candidates will have their microphones muted when it's not their turn to speak.
  • Candidates will stand behind their lecturns for the duration of the debate.
  • Candidates will be provided a pen, a pad of paper, and a bottle of water.
  • Candidates will not be allowed to have props or pre-written notes.
  • Candidates will not receive topics or questions in advance.
  • Campaign staff will not be allowed to interact with candidates during commercial breaks.
  • President Trump won the coin toss and elected to give the last closing statement.
  • Vice President Harris chose the lecturn on the viewers' right.
  • Lecturns will be sized according to the height of each candidate.
